Over 10 days, with a cumulative elevation gain of over 4,000 meters, join the Garmin Cycling Club to experience the beauty of Taiwan through cycling!

Garmin invited ambassadors from GCC across 8 Asian regions to join us in a clockwise journey around Taiwan, starting from the north. With the GroupRide feature activated on the Garmin Edge cycling computer, we explored Taiwan’s renowned cycling routes by pedaling. 

We conquered many famous mountain routes and marveled at the breathtaking coastal scenery of eastern Taiwan, where mountains meet the sea. Despite occasional rain and wind, we pressed on fearlessly, embracing nature’s warm welcome and proving that cyclists are truly waterproof. 

Beyond cycling, we also joined the Hotel Royal Group’s City Awakening Project for a morning tour, soaking in the dawn of various Taiwanese cities and diving deeper into Taiwan’s culture and urban life.

